\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces  Example of OH emission modeling and subtraction for the full set of extracted spectra. Each panel shows a one-dimensional spectrum as a function of wavelength, illustrating the dense forest of atmospheric emission lines and their removal by the pipeline. The subtraction is performed using an iterative, locally constrained Gaussian modeling of emission features combined with a two-pass continuum estimation. The resulting spectra exhibit a strong suppression of sky emission lines while preserving the underlying continuum and astrophysical features, with no evidence of systematic oversubtraction. }}{3}{}\protected@file@percent }
