\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces  Mosaic of final flux-calibrated spectra for all slits in the Dolidze~25 dataset. The spectra are shown as a function of wavelength (in nm) and flux, after full processing including extraction, OH emission subtraction, telluric correction, and photometric flux calibration. The consistency of spectral shapes and flux levels across slits demonstrates the robustness of the pipeline, while the diversity of spectral features reflects the range of stellar properties in the observed field. }}{5}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:final}{{7}{5}{}{figure.7}{}}
\@LN@col{2}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces  Step08 wavelength-attachment and alignment diagnostics. The figure shows the normalized spectra of all slits overplotted in the wavelength region of the O$_2$ A band after wavelength vectors have been attached to the extracted one-dimensional spectra. The close alignment of the telluric absorption feature across slits demonstrates the internal consistency of the wavelength solution and provides a direct validation of the extraction and wavelength-assignment stages prior to OH subtraction. }}{5}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:extraction}{{8}{5}{}{figure.8}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces  Measured wavelength of the O$_2$ A-band minimum as a function of slit number for the Step08 wavelength-attached spectra. The scatter provides a compact quantitative diagnostic of the slit-to-slit consistency of the wavelength solution before subsequent sky-emission and telluric corrections are applied. }}{5}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:extraction_scatter}{{9}{5}{}{figure.9}{}}
